@startuml
' MeCab processing pipeline for xer

title xer MeCab processing pipeline

skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName Monospaced
skinparam defaultTextAlignment center
skinparam rectangle {
  BackgroundColor #FFFDE7
  BorderColor #444444
  RoundCorner 8
}
skinparam note {
  BackgroundColor #F5F5F5
  BorderColor #777777
}
skinparam arrow {
  Color #AA0055
  Thickness 1
}
left to right direction

rectangle "UTF-8 source text\nstd::u8string_view" as Source
rectangle "mecab_parse(text, options)\nreturns: result<vector<mecab_token>>" as Parse
note bottom of Parse
- resolves mecab executable
- launches mecab as a child process
- sends UTF-8 input
- validates UTF-8 output
end note

rectangle "vector<mecab_token>\n- surface\n- feature\n- features: mecab_features" as Tokens
rectangle "mecab_split_phrases(tokens)\nreturns: vector<mecab_phrase>" as Phrases
note bottom of Phrases
Practical phrase ranges
- bunsetsu-like ranges
- symbol ranges
end note

rectangle "mecab_to_kana(tokens, kana_options)\nreturns: u8string" as ToKana
note bottom of ToKana
Uses MeCab readings
Optional particle reading correction
end note

rectangle "mecab_kana_wakati(tokens, kana_options)\nreturns: u8string" as KanaWakati
rectangle "mecab_romaji_wakati(tokens, romaji_options)\nreturns: result<u8string>" as RomajiWakati
rectangle "mecab_braille_wakati(tokens, kana_options)\nreturns: result<u8string>" as BrailleWakati
rectangle "mecab_ip_braille_wakati(tokens, kana_options)\nreturns: result<u8string>" as IpBrailleWakati

note right of KanaWakati
Combines:
- phrase ranges
- kana conversion
- spaces between phrases
end note

note right of RomajiWakati
Combines:
- phrase ranges
- kana conversion
- strtoctrans / romaji conversion
- symbol ranges kept as surface text
end note

note right of BrailleWakati
Combines:
- phrase ranges
- kana conversion
- Japanese punctuation handling
- ASCII fragment conversion
- <xer/braille.h>
end note

note right of IpBrailleWakati
Same as braille_wakati,
but ASCII fragments use
information-processing braille
end note

rectangle "mecab_braille_translate(text, parse_options, kana_options)\nreturns: result<u8string>" as BrailleTranslate
rectangle "mecab_ip_braille_translate(text, parse_options, kana_options)\nreturns: result<u8string>" as IpBrailleTranslate
note bottom of BrailleTranslate
Convenience wrapper:
parse + braille_wakati
end note
note bottom of IpBrailleTranslate
Convenience wrapper:
parse + ip_braille_wakati
end note

Source --> Parse
Parse --> Tokens
Tokens --> Phrases
Tokens --> ToKana

Tokens --> KanaWakati
Phrases --> KanaWakati
ToKana --> KanaWakati

Tokens --> RomajiWakati
Phrases --> RomajiWakati
ToKana --> RomajiWakati

Tokens --> BrailleWakati
Phrases --> BrailleWakati
ToKana --> BrailleWakati

Tokens --> IpBrailleWakati
Phrases --> IpBrailleWakati
ToKana --> IpBrailleWakati

Source --> BrailleTranslate
BrailleTranslate ..> Parse : internally uses
BrailleTranslate ..> BrailleWakati : then calls

Source --> IpBrailleTranslate
IpBrailleTranslate ..> Parse : internally uses
IpBrailleTranslate ..> IpBrailleWakati : then calls

legend bottom
|= Layer |= Main role |
| Parse | Run MeCab and build tokens |
| Phrase | Derive practical phrase ranges |
| Kana | Convert token readings to kana |
| Output helpers | Build kana / romaji / braille wakachi-gaki |
| Convenience wrappers | Parse text and convert directly |
endlegend

@enduml
